From d5a2412ce92f4394f965fbb1378c25593efb19ed Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kagura-agent <kagura.agent.ai@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 16:36:24 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] refactor(ws): scope gateway events by guild membership
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Track guild IDs on GatewaySession (populated during IDENTIFY)
- GatewayDispatcher now accepts ChannelsRepo for channel→guild resolution
- broadcastToGuild: MESSAGE_CREATE/UPDATE/DELETE, CHANNEL_UPDATE, TYPING_START
  only reach sessions whose guildIds includes the event's guild
- broadcastToGuildMembers: PRESENCE_UPDATE only reaches sessions
  sharing at least one guild with the user going online/offline
- READY presences filtered to users sharing guilds with the connector
- REQUEST_TYPING validates guild membership before broadcasting
- Add gateway.test.ts with guild-scoped broadcasting tests

Closes #173
